## 🔧 Environment Variables

### Backend `.env`
```env
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/rbac-portal
JWT_SECRET=your-secure-secret-key
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
SESSION_SECRET=your-session-secret
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=xxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxx
GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:5000/api/auth/google/callback
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

### Frontend `.env`
```env
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
```

---

## 🌐 Deployment

### Backend (Render / Railway / EC2)
- Set all env variables in the platform dashboard
- Change `GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL` to your production URL
- Change `CLIENT_URL` to your frontend URL
- MongoDB Atlas recommended for production

### Frontend (Vercel / Netlify)
- Set `REACT_APP_API_URL` to your production API URL
- Add your domain to Google OAuth Authorized Origins

---

## 🧩 Extending the Portal

### Adding a new protected route
```jsx
// In App.js
<Route path="/analytics" element={
  <ProtectedRoute requiredPermission="analytics:read">
    <AnalyticsPage />
  </ProtectedRoute>
} />
```

### Adding a new permission check in backend
```js
// In any route file
router.get('/reports', authenticate, requirePermission('reports:read'), getReports);
```

### Adding a new role
```js
// In User.js model - update the enum and rolePermissions object
role: { type: String, enum: [..., 'new_role'] }
```